title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
message: Going through the rails, everything above pp5v_s5_LDO is stable, PP5v_s5_LDO jumps a bit when the fan pulses, from 4.89vto 5v.  Every voltage below that pulses.  Everything appears to be trying to come on.  Is there a standard way of attacking 1/4 fan spin?

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
message: If the fan pulses then all rails will be pulsing too. Was this liquid? Is CPU Vcore pulsing too?

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
message: Yes liquid, CPU Vcore is pulsing too.

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
message: If there was liquid in the U2600 area this would be a very good 1st suspect.

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
message: area had a little water damage, went ahead and cleaned up from a donor just in case. Still has the 1/4 fan spin.

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
message: U2600 was replaced now? R7402/03 ok?

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin

title: 820-3115 1/4 fan spin
